<h1>HackerspaceSG Incorporation</h1>
<br />
<div id="displaycontent">
<p style="font-weight: bold;"><a target="_blank" href="http://hackerspace.sg/">Hackerspace.SG</a> Incorporation</p>
<p>Owner: Ruiwen</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Done.</span> Decide on a corporate form and incorporate "<a target="_blank" href="http://hackerspace.sg/">Hackerspace.SG</a> Pte Ltd" or Ltd or LLP.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Open bank account. 7pm Thursday.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Keep basic ledger on <a target="_blank" href="http://spreadsheets.google.com/">spreadsheets.google.com</a> to track the membership dues and expenses.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.5em;">Corporate Form</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">Meng and Ruiwen incorporated on 20091014:</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;"><span style="font-family: monospace;">Company No. :200919232E</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: monospace;">NOTICE OF INCORPORATION</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: monospace;">This is to confirm that</span> <a target="_blank" href="http://hackerspace.sg/" style="font-family: monospace;">HACKERSPACE.SG</a> <span style="font-family: monospace;">PTE. LTD. is incorporated under the Companies Act(Cap.50), on and from 14/10/2009 and that the Company is a PRIVATE COMPANY LIMITED BY SHARES.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">Until we are a few months farther along, it would be OK to operate the Hackerspace Membership roster separately from the Pte Ltd shareholder roster or from the LLP partner roster.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">Ruiwen and his buddies can be shareholders if they want.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">Ordinary memberships should initially be managed separately from the legal membership.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">Down the road we can harmonize the legal shareholder/partners and the membership.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">So we would be more like a gym than a country club at first.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">The company would have no employees.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.5em;">Bank Account</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">Meng would be OK with any local bank ... preferably with a good online bookkeeping system, that can export transactions to Quicken or XLS.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1em;">Standard Chartered</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.standardchartered.com.sg/sme-banking/cash-management/essential-lite.html">http://www.standardchartered.com.sg/sme-banking/cash-management/essential-lite.html</a></p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">no minimum balance. transaction logs can be downloaded as CSV.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1em;">DBS</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">A minimum deposit of SGD3,000 and a minimum monthly balance of SGD10,000 is required.</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;"><strong>UOB</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">Minimum Minimum Monthly Average Balance $20,000</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">http://www.uob.com.sg/corporate/corporate/deposits/current_account.html</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1em;">Decision</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;">Open Standard Chartered account.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Key Item:</span> Obtain and post instructions for direct funds transfers from other bank accounts in SG into the company account.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left; direction: ltr; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.5em;">Appoint a Secretary</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Deadline 60 days iirc. For now ask Kelvin to volunteer?</p>

